{
  "stem": "1753.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I was demobilized, I was discharged the rank of corporal-- a very low rank, but just fine for me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, of course, you know, we were stationed on the east side of the Vistula River near Warszawa Praga.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we were waiting-- we were anxious to-- it was a very, very cold winter, incidentally, and the Vistula was frozen solid.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We could have easily walked across.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we didn't understand why we were stationed there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't move.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had no order to cross the river to take in Warsaw while the Germans were battling the partisans on the other side.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Afterwards, it was explained to us the people that rose up against the Nazis, in fact, was a group of Poles that took their orders from the exiled government [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] of the Polish government from 1939 that escaped to London.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, subsequently, we realized that one was our-- our army.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were-- we took our orders from the Russians, which, in fact, the Armia Ludowa, the People's Army, while the others were-- were the-- the-- from under the direction of General Anders from the-- the Polish Army in exile in London.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So the Russians felt let them killed himself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Then we walk in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In fact, that's exactly what happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The Germans and the-- the-- the-- the group that rose up, they-- they killed each other.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then we moved in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But that already-- that was-- in-- and we moved in, I believe, it was late January, early February, of 19-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in 1945.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then after that, I was stationed in various barracks in various divisional areas in Poland such as Inowroclaw, Bydgoszcz, Torun, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] and finally and I was discharged in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
